    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Then it’s just a simple matter of saving each region out as a separate image file. And since we know each image should contain four letters from left-to-right, we can use that knowledge to label the letters as we save them. As long as we save them out in that order, we should be saving each image letter with the proper letter name.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
